dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: Angular_Distance_Index

class.title: MiniTES_Coordinate_Parameters

attribute.title: angular_distance
attribute.description: The amount of radians to move around the RAT revolve axis before a scan completes or amount of radians to move before moving the RAT z-axis down one step.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: angular_distance_name
attribute.description: The name of the operation with the RAT revolve motor movement.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The operation was a RAT grind.
The operation was a RAT dwell.

attribute.title: download_priority
attribute.description: The download_priority attribute specifies which data to downlink/transmit, based on order of importance. The lower numerical priority (higher-ranked number) data products are transmitted before higher numerical priority (lower-ranked number) data products. For example, an image with a downlink priority of 24 will be transmitted before an image with a downlink priority of 62. The allowable range is 0 to 99.

attribute.title: local_true_solar_time_sol
attribute.description: The local_true_solar_time_sol element specifies the number of solar days elapsed since a reference day (e.g. the day on which a landing vehicle set down) for local true solar time (LTST). Days are measured in rotations of the planet in question from midnight to midnight. The reference day is '1', as landing day is Sol 1.

attribute.title: magnet_id
attribute.description: The magnet_id specifies a magnet that is visible in an image or measured by an instrument.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Target is the capture magnet located at the base of the PMA.
Target is the filter magnet located at the base of the PMA.
Target is the sweep magnet located at the rear of the rover deck next to the Pancam calibration target.
Target is one or more of the magnets mounted on the outer ring of the RAT.

attribute.title: mission_phase_name
attribute.description: The mission_phase_name identifies a time period within the mission.

attribute.title: producer_institution_name
attribute.description: The producer_institution_name specifies the identity of the facility or institution that produced the product.

attribute.title: product_type
attribute.description: The product_type identifies a group of data products within a collection that have some property in common, such as processing level, resolution, or instrument-specific setting.

attribute.title: product_version_id
attribute.description: The product_version_id specifies the version of the product. It usually begins with a 'V' and followed by an identifier for the controlling camera SIS.

attribute.title: release_id
attribute.description: Release_id is the identifier of a scheduled release of MER data from PDS. The first MER data release is Release 0001. The release_id for a given product is always the first release in which it appears, and does not change if the product is revised later.

attribute.title: sol_number
attribute.description: Sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which an observation was acquired. Landing day is Sol 1.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_count_partition
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_count_partition provides the clock partition active for the spacecraft_clock_start_count and spacecraft_clock_stop_count attributes. This attribute may be used when the spacecraft_clock values do not include a partition number.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_start_count is the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of an observation. It represents the number of ticks. If a fractional value is present, in some cases it means a true decimal fraction (i.e. milliseconds) while in other cases it stands for a count of 1/256th of a second (which stems from the fact that the fractional part was represented by a single byte in the original telemetry stream.) When comparing SCLK times or converting them to other time systems, it is important to know which of the two representations the SCLK string follows. Normally the documentation accompanying a particular data set defines which type of SCLK fractional part was used in that data set.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The spacecraft_clock_stop_count is the value of the spacecraft clock at the end of an observation. It represents the number of ticks. If a fractional value is present, in some cases it means a true decimal fraction (i.e. milliseconds) while in other cases it stands for a count of 1/256th of a second (which stems from the fact that the fractional part was represented by a single byte in the original telemetry stream.) When comparing SCLK times or converting them to other time systems, it is important to know which of the two representations the SCLK string follows. Normally the documentation accompanying a particular data set defines which type of SCLK fractional part was used in that data set.

attribute.title: cal_co_add
attribute.description: Commanded number of calibration observations to average together.

attribute.title: cal_dwell
attribute.description: Commanded value of the number of icks to acquire during a calibration observation.

attribute.title: cal_frequency
attribute.description: Commanded value of the minimum number of icks between internal calibration looks.

attribute.title: center_azimuth
attribute.description: The commanded center azimuth of the acquired data.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: center_elevation
attribute.description: The commanded center elevation of the acquired data.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: co_add
attribute.description: Commanded number of spectra to average together.

attribute.title: columns
attribute.description: Commanded value of the number of columns (azimuth steps) to acquire.

attribute.title: dwell
attribute.description: Commanded value of the number of icks to acquire at one azimuth/elevation position.

attribute.title: high_channel
attribute.description: Commanded value of the end channel number to acquire minus one.

attribute.title: horizontal_space
attribute.description: Commanded value of the horizontal spacing between consecutive columns.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: low_channel
attribute.description: Commanded value of the start channel number to acquire. Channel numbers start at zero.

attribute.title: phase_algorithm_name
attribute.description: Commanded value of the phase correction algorithm to use on board.

attribute.title: rows
attribute.description: Commanded value of the number of rows (elevation steps) to acquire.

attribute.title: vertical_space
attribute.description: Commanded value of the vertical spacing between consecutive rows.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: zone2_width
attribute.description: Commanded length of the center-burst region of the interferogram, which is compressed separately from zone1 and zone-3.

attribute.title: coordinate_name
attribute.description: Name associated with each coordinate in the Coordinate_Parameters class.

attribute.title: coordinate_unit
attribute.description: The unit for the coordinate value by coordinate_name in the Coordinate_Parameters class.

attribute.title: coordinate_value
attribute.description: The value of the coordinate named by coordinate_name in the Coordinate_Parameters class.

attribute.title: coordinate_id
attribute.description: Identifies the frame in which the coordinate values are given.

attribute.title: field_of_view
attribute.description: The instantaneous field of view of the instrument that was used while acquiring the data.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The field of view was 8 mrad.
The field of view was 20 mrad.

attribute.title: gain_state
attribute.description: Specifies the gain state of the MiniTES analog signal amplifier.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The gain state parameter was set to low.
The gain state parameter was set to high.

attribute.title: laser_1_status_flag
attribute.description: Status of the primary laser. Only onen laser can be on at one time.

attribute.title: laser_2_status_flag
attribute.description: Status of the backup laser. Only onen laser can be on at one time.

attribute.title: laser_heater_status_flag
attribute.description: The status of the laser heater.

attribute.title: linear_motor_status_flag
attribute.description: Provides the status of the Michelson motor.

attribute.title: optical_switch_state
attribute.description: Indicates which of the optical switches was used by the miniTES optical mirror. There are two switches for redundancy in case one fails.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The primary optical switch was used while acquired the data.
The redundant optical switch was used while acquired the data.

attribute.title: spare_bit_flag
attribute.description: The status of the spare bit within the command word.

attribute.description: The angular velocity used in the operation of the RAT revolve axis.

attribute.title: rotation_voltage
attribute.description: Value of the voltage applied to the RAT grinding wheel rotation motor.
